<mjml>
  <mj-head>
    <mj-style> h2, img, p { margin: 0; } p { margin-bottom: 10px; } </mj-style>
    <!-- <mj-font name="Roboto+Serif" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto+Serif" /> -->
    <mj-font
      name="Roboto+Serif"
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?faily=Roboto+Serif:ital,opsz,wght@0,8..144,100..900;1,8..144,100..900&display=swap"
    />
  </mj-head>
  <mj-body background-color="#f9f8f9">
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
    <!-- Header -->
    <mj-section
      background-color="#eff1f4"
      css-class="border-line"
      padding="1px 0.5px 1px 1px"
      border-radius="5px"
    >
      <mj-column background-color="#fff" border-radius="5px" padding="0px">
        <mj-spacer height="16px" />
        <mj-image
          padding="10px 12px 6px 12px"
          css-class="light_img"
          width="150px"
          src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/logo.png"
          href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com"
          alt=""
        />

        <mj-divider
          border-width="1px"
          border-style="solid"
          border-color="lightgrey"
          padding="0px 12px 10px 12px"
        />
        <mj-text
          padding="0px 12px 0px 12px "
          font-family="Roboto+Serif"
          color="#000000"
        >
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; margin-top: 2px">
            Presidential Summary is as big as 🇰🇾 Cayman Islands.
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;
                color: black;
              "
              href="mailto:?subject=Check%20out%20Presidential%20Summary&body=Hey,%0A%0AI’ve%20been%20reading%20this%20newsletter%20called%20Presidential%20Summary,%20and%20I%20think%20you’d%20find%20it%20super%20useful.%20It’s%20quick,%20clear,%20and%20gives%20you%20the%20day’s%20most%20important%20news%20without%20spin%20or%20fluff.%0A%0AHere’s%20the%20link%20to%20check%20it%20out%20and%20subscribe:%0A👉%20https://presidentialsummary.com"
              target="_blank"
              >Share us</a
            >
            with your friends and let's reach the size of 🇦🇩 Andorra next.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>In this edition:</strong>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-table
          font-family="Roboto+Serif"
          cellpadding="0"
          cellspacing="0"
          padding="0px 18px 0px 18px"
          style="width: 100%"
        >
          <tr>
            <td
              style="
                font-size: 18px;
                width: 20px;
                vertical-align: top;
                padding-right: 8px;
                line-height: 1.6;
              "
            >
              →
            </td>
            <td style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6">
              Trump revokes education freeze
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td
              style="
                font-size: 18px;
                width: 20px;
                vertical-align: top;
                padding-right: 8px;
                line-height: 1.6;
              "
            >
              →
            </td>
            <td style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; line-height: 1.6">
              Greece and Turkey battle flames
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td
              style="
                font-size: 18px;
                width: 20px;
                vertical-align: top;
                padding-right: 8px;
                line-height: 1.6;
              "
            >
              →
            </td>
            <td style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; line-height: 1.6">
              Google missed earthquake alerts
            </td>
          </tr>
        </mj-table>

        <!-- <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" /> -->
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- Header -->
    <!-- breaking news-->
    <!-- /breaking news -->
    <mj-spacer height="10px" />
    <!-- Spotlight -->
    <mj-section
      background-color="#eff1f4"
      css-class="border-line"
      padding="1px 0.5px 1px 1px"
      border-radius="5px"
    >
      <mj-column background-color="#fff" border-radius="5px" padding="0px">
        <mj-text
          padding="16px 12px 10px 12px"
          font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;"
          color="white"
        >
          <h2
            style="
              padding-bottom: 8px;
              color: #4d3060;
              text-align: left;
              border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;

              font-size: 26px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
            "
          >
            Spotlight
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text
          padding="10px 12px"
          font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;"
          color="#000000"
        >
          <h2
            style="
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            "
          >
            US-EU trade pact
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image
          border-radius="10px"
          padding="10px 12px"
          width="600px"
          src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/us-eu-trade-agreement-von-der-leyen.jpg"
          alt="Von der Leyen said the deal would bring “stability” and “predictability,” and other European leaders have broadly welcomed the development"
          href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com"
        />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #a9a7af">
            <i
              >Von der Leyen said the agreement would bring “stability” and
              “predictability,” and other European leaders have broadly welcomed
              the development. Credits: Evelyn Hockstein/Reuters</i
            >
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            President Trump announced a framework for the
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-28-jul-25-spotlight-h1-1-biggest-trade-agreement-between-the-us-and-the-eu?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >biggest trade agreement between the US and the EU</a
            >, which includes a latest 15% levy on most imports, including cars,
            pharmaceuticals, and semiconductors. In return, the EU has committed
            to purchasing $750B worth of US energy and investing another $600B
            into the US economy.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            With this agreement, both sides are avoiding a 30% tariff Trump had
            threatened to impose on August 1 if talks failed. It also opens EU
            markets to American goods at zero tariffs and includes large-scale
            purchases of US military equipment. Export-heavy EU members, like
            Germany and Ireland, are welcoming the outcome, which spares them
            harsher trade penalties.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; filter: blur(5px)">
            Meanwhile, the US braces for a
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #4d3060;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-28-jul-25-spotlight-h1-2-pivotal-week?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >pivotal week</a
            >
            for its economy. Key economic data on inflation, jobs, GDP, and
            trade flows are set to be released, while the Federal Reserve will
            decide whether to cut interest or resist until it can assess the
            impact of Trump’s policies.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
  </mj-body>
</mjml>
